course.subject: SOSC
course.name: Categorical Data Analysis
course.description: This seminar will focus on sociological (and other social scientific) applications of limited-dependent and qualitative variables.  A family of statistical models, including logit/probit models, log-linear models, one-dimensional and multidimensional association models, multinomial logistic and probit models, ordered logit and probit models, and models with sample selection and truncation.  The only prerequisite of the class is that students must have already taken courses on multiple regression (SOSC 5090) or its equivalent.
